I don't think it's available any freaking where to watch. Which is such a shame. But this one here, Dastak, is a rare cinema gem. It makes you go inside the minds of the protagonists and see them slide continuously.

Ek aadmi aur uski aurat ka man, unka dhairya, unka pyar, unki maryada, unki sanskriti, unke usool... kaise toot te hi jate hain. Ye dekhte hi banta hai.

Just to get you started. A newly married lower middle class couple doesn't want to live in the slums so they rent a really small flat in the adjoining neighbourhood in Mumbai. The catches are: the hood is a red light area (which is why they can afford the rent) and the flat they manage to get used to be a kotha. Wahin se shuru hoti hai Dastak. Aur unka moral decrepitude. Gooseflesh stuff this!

